cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The problem also involves databases and efficient retrieval, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) as possible categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical proofs and analysis, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
